Package remodel.expr

Interface PriorityCodes

All Known Implementing Classes:
ApplicationExpression, AssignmentExpression, BinaryExpression, BracketedExpression, CompoundExpression, ConditionalExpression, CreationExpression, Expression, IdentifierExpression, InvocationExpression, LambdaExpression, LiteralExpression, MultipleExpression, OperatorExpression, UnaryExpression, WrappedExpression
public interface PriorityCodes
PriorityCodes defines a set of codes denoting order of precedence. Every kind of Expression has one of these levels of priority. The higher the priority, the more strongly the Expression binds its operands (if any).
Version:
1.0
Author:
Anthony J H Simons
